      "role": "user",
      "content": "That's really useful, thanks for continuing. My students are also worried about the rebuttal phase where the opposition will likely claim these arguments are basically just a way to justify xenophobia or exclusion. \n\nHow should they respond to the claim that prioritizing \"cultural distinctiveness\" or \"sovereignty\" is just a moral mask for being anti-immigrant? I want them to be able to explain why these are legitimate political/legal principles rather than just being seen as being \"intolerant.\"",
